This feature exist in Jet brains products and I find it very useful to refactoring your code.
Basically you :
1. select a piece of code 
2. click on some short key (let's say ctrl+alt+v || ctrl+alt+m) 
3. choose a name for the variable or method (if method choose also the scope) 
4. replace the selected or all occurrences of the code with the variable (or method call)

Example: 
```
var arr = [1,2,3,4,5,6,7];
for( var i = 0; i< arr.length; i++){
 var a = arr[i];
 var b = arr[i] *2;
 console.log(a,b);
}
```

in this case if we select `arr[i];` , click ctrl+alt+v , type in 'value', we will get

```
var arr = [1,2,3,4,5,6,7];
for( var i = 0; i< arr.length; i++){
 var value = arr[i];
 var a = value ;
 var b = value  *2;
 console.log(a,b);
}
```
